DOC.brief_summary: The purpose of this study is to compare concurrent oxytocin with membrane sweeping versus dinoprostone pessary in labor induction for multiparas at term with an unfavorable cervix.
DOC.brief_title: Concurrent Oxytocin With Membrane Sweeping Versus Dinoprostone Pessary in Labor Induction of Multiparous Women at Term
DOC.criteria: singleton pregnancy Multiparous women gestational age >=37.0 weeks Bishop score <=6 intact amniotic membrane absence of labor live fetus with vertex presentation no previous uterine surgical procedure Multiple pregnancy Placenta previa
